
[1]habituate

   HABIT'UATE, v.t.

   1. To accustom; to make familiar by frequent use or practice. Men may
   habituate themselves to the taste of oil or tobacco. They habituate
   themselves to vice. Let us habituate ourselves and our children to the
   exercise of charity.

   2. To settle as an inhabitant in a place.

                    HABIT'UATE, a. Inveterate by custom.

   1. Formed by habit.
